Wengie: So, there's a way to never lose in Tic - Tac - Toe, you basically either win or draw a 100% of the time, if you go first,  take the center square, if your opponent takes the side square, then you automatically win by picking a corner square, which they'll need to block, and then, you can win by picking a square, that gives you two giving options, here, and here, which they won't be able to stop, if your opponent takes a corner square, then you're most likely end in a draw,  but, taking the opposing corner square gives you a small chance of winning, 
 if they take a side square!

Wengie: If you go second, you'll need to either take the middle square if they didn't take it first turn, or a corner square, if they took the middle square, so then, your next move depends on theirs, but with that start, you should never lose if you play the rest of the gam smartly!
